               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Ṣalota kidān za-nagh "Morning Prayer of the Covenant" (fols. 2ra –
                     8ra, l.7)
 II) Anaphoras (fols. 8ra – 22va, 91ra – 124va)
 II-1)
                     Anaphora of Our Lady by St Cyriacus of Behnesa (fols. 8ra, l.8 – 22va,
                     l.14)
 III) Ṣalota ʿǝṭān "Prayer of the Incense" (fols. 22vb, l.1 – 53rb,
                     l.13)
 IV) Śǝrʿāta qǝddāse “Ordinary of the Mass” (fols. 53rb, l.14 – 91va,
                     l.3)
 II-2) Anaphora of the Apostles (fols. 91ra, l.4 – 106vb, l.10)
                     II-3) Anaphora of St Jacob of Serug (fols. 106vb, l.11 – 114vb, l.12)
                     II-4) Anaphora of Our Lord Jesus Christ (fols. 114vb, l.13 – 120ra, l.16)
                     II-5) Anaphora of St Dioscorus (fols. 120rb, l.1 – 124ra, l.9; the ʾAnbǝro ʾǝd
                     of this Anaphora is added after the colophon, s. Additio 1)
 
 Additio
                     1; colophon.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">

                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                     <colophon xml:id="coloph1">
                        <locus target="#124ra">124ra</locus>: ዝ፡ ቅዳሴ፡ ዘሰሀስሕለ፡ ቂርቆስ፡ ዘተጽሕፈ፡ በንዋዩ፡ ዘጸሐፎ፡
                        &lt;...&gt;እም፡ አመ፡ ጸአቱ፡ ብሔረ፡ ኢትዮጵያ፡ ለጳጳስ፡ አቡነ፡ ሰላማ፡ ዳግማዊ፡ በ፳ወ፪፡ ዓመት፡ ወመንፈቀ፡
                        ዓመት፡ እም፡ አመ፡ ነግሠ፡ ንጉሠ፡ ነገሥት፡ ቴዎድሮስ፡ በ፲ወ፪፡ ዓመት፡ ዘሰረቆ፡ ወዘፈሀቆ፡ ውጉዘ፡ ይኩን፡
                        በሦልጣነ[sic]፡ ጴጥሮስ፡ ወጳውሎስ፨<locus target="#124ra">124ra</locus>: This Missal is of
                        Sahasǝḥlä Qirqos, which was written with its own money; the one who wrote it is
                        &lt;...&gt;, in the 22th year and a half after the arrival of the bishop ʾabuna
                        salāma II in the land of Ethiopia, and 12 after the enthronement of the King of
                        Kings Tewodros. He who steals it or erases [its text] shall be excommunicated
                        by the authority of Peter and Paul. The name of the scribe has been effaced.
                     </colophon>
                  </msItem>
                  
