                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Mediocre.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black; reddish-brown.</seg>The name of the scribe has been
                        effaced from the colophon.<date>Middle 19th century.</date>
                        <list type="abbreviations">
                           <item>ይካ፡ for ይቤ፡ ካህን፡</item>
                           <item>ይዲ፡ for ይቤ፡ ዲያቆን፡</item>
                           <item>ይሕ፡ for ይቤ፡ ሕዝብ፡</item>
                           <item>በእ፡ for በእንተ፡</item>
                           <item>ወእ፡ for ወእምዝ፡</item>
                        </list>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; incipits and headings of the texts;
                           the words መፍቀሬ፡ አምላክ፡ standing for the name of the reigning monarch;
                           directives for the ministers (e.g., fol. 51vb); names of the patriarch
                           and metropolitan; names of the donors mentioned at the beginning of the
                           Anaphoras; names of the Evangelists (e.g., fols. 86v-87r); the words
                           ቡራኬ፡, ዕማሬ፡ (እማሬ፡), በእንተ፡, ወእምዝ፡; the word ርኁቀ፡ in: ይበል፡ ቀሲስ፡ … በለኈሳስ፡
                           ርኁቀ፡ (e.g., fol.84vb, l.12); abbreviations; elements of the punctuation
                           signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals; some of the corrections written
                           above or beside the words (e.g., fols. 8vb, 9ra).</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
