                        <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0042MR">Mǝdra Ruba /MR</placeName>
                     </origPlace>
                     <origDate notBefore="1863" notAfter="1867">According to the colopnon, the book
                        was written 22,5 years after the coming of ʾabuna salāma (in office 1841-67;
                        he is mentioned elsewhere, e.g., <locus target="#9ra">9ra</locus>); and 12
                        years after the coronation of King Tewodros II (r. 1855-68). The resulting
                        dates are 1863 and 1867.</origDate>
                  </origin>
               <provenance>Some persons are mentioned in the
                     supplications at the beginning and at the end of the Anaphoras: ʾabuna Walda Tǝnśāʾe (8rb, 106vb), ʾabuna Gabra Śǝllāse
                        (91va), Walda Gabrǝʾel (106vb), Walda Qirqos (106vb), Walda
                     ʿAbiyä ʾƎgziʾ (106vb, 120rb), ʾabuna Gabra Ḥǝywat (106vb). In the colophon, Sähasǝḥlä Qirqos (a church
                     or monastery, or a personal name?) is mentioned as the original owner of the
                     Ms.</provenance></history>
